The present value annuity refers to the present value of all future cash payments based on the given rates and time frame. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value annuity}&=\text{Payment}\times\dfrac{1-\frac{1}{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}}}{\text{rate}}
\end{aligned}$$
